<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12140e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12140e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12140e"> 140(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> roadside burial / so that after 4 days / spirit reenters / passing W</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The idea of reincarnation is widespread. &hellip; The Huron also believed in reincarnation, for <mark>they used to bury the bodies of little children by the roadside, in the hope that they would enter passing women and thus be born</mark>. They also possessed a set of names for each clan, all derived from the characteristics of the clan totem, from which names the council women of the clan chose one for each child. <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 145-6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
